00038 #define FAILIF(cond) do {} while ((cond) && fatal(__func__, __LINE__))
00039 #define CHKSYS(res) FAILIF((res) == -1)
00040 #define CHKPTR(p)   FAILIF((p) == NULL)

00052 int
00053 test_inserts_from_stdin(void)
00054 {
00055     struct ccn_charbuf *c = NULL;
00056     struct ccn_charbuf *f = NULL;
00057     int delete;      /* Lines ending with a '!' are to be deleted instead */
00058     int i;
00059     int item = 0;
00060     int dups = 0;
00061     int unique = 0;
00062     int deleted = 0;
00063     int missing = 0;
00064     ccn_cookie cookie = 0;
00065     ccn_cookie ocookie = 0;
00066     struct ccn_nametree *ntree = NULL;
00067     struct ccny *node = NULL;
00068     unsigned char *p = NULL;
00069     
00070     ntree = ccn_nametree_create(42);
00071     CHKPTR(ntree);
00072     ccn_nametree_check(ntree);
00073     c = ccn_charbuf_create();
00074     CHKPTR(c);
00075     f = ccn_charbuf_create();
00076     CHKPTR(f);
00077     CHKPTR(ccn_charbuf_reserve(c, 8800));
00078     while (fgets((char *)c->buf, c->limit, stdin)) {
00079         item++;
00080         c->length = strlen((char *)c->buf);
00081         if (c->length > 0 && c->buf[c->length - 1] == '\n')
00082             c->length--;
00083         // printf("%9d %s\n", item, ccn_charbuf_as_string(c));
00084         delete = 0;
00085         if (c->length > 0 && c->buf[c->length - 1] == '!') {
00086             delete = 1;
00087             c->length--;
00088         }
00089         /* Turn the string into a valid flatname, one byte per component */
00090         ccn_charbuf_reset(f);
00091         p = ccn_charbuf_reserve(f, 2 * c->length);
00092         for (i = 0; i < c->length; i++) {
00093             p[2 * i] = 1;
00094             p[2 * i + 1] = c->buf[i];
00095         }
00096         f->length = 2 * c->length;
00097         node = ccn_nametree_lookup(ntree, f->buf, f->length);
00098         cookie = ccny_cookie(node);
00099         if (0) ccn_nametree_check(ntree);
00100         if (delete) {
00101             if (cookie != 0) {
00102                 ccny_remove(ntree, node);
00103                 ccny_destroy(ntree, &node);
00104                 FAILIF(node != NULL);
00105                 deleted++;
00106             }
00107             else
00108                 missing++;
00109             continue;
00110         }
00111         /* insert case */
00112         node = ccny_create(lrand48(), 0);
00113         ccny_set_key(node, f->buf, f->length);
00114         if (ntree->n >= ntree->limit) {
00115             int res = ccn_nametree_grow(ntree);
00116             FAILIF(res != 0);
00117             fprintf(stderr, "n=%d, limit=%d\n", ntree->n, ntree->limit);
00118         }
00119         ocookie = ccny_enroll(ntree, node);
00120         if (cookie != 0) {
00121             FAILIF(ocookie != cookie);
00122             ccny_destroy(ntree, &node);
00123             FAILIF(node != NULL);
00124             dups++;
00125         }
00126         else {
00127             FAILIF(ccny_cookie(node) == 0);
00128             unique++;
00129         }
00130     }
00131     ccn_nametree_check(ntree);
00132     printf("%d unique, %d duplicate, %d deleted, %d missing\n",
00133                unique,    dups,         deleted,    missing);
00134     printf("Nametree nodes:");
00135     for (node = ccn_nametree_first(ntree); node != NULL; node = ccny_next(node))
00136         printf(" %u", ccny_cookie(node));
00137     printf("\n");
00138     printf("Reversed nodes:");
00139     for (node = ccn_nametree_last(ntree); node != NULL; node = ccny_prev(node))
00140         printf(" %u", ccny_cookie(node));
00141     printf("\n");
00142     FAILIF(unique - deleted != ntree->n);
00143     ccn_nametree_destroy(&ntree);
00144     ccn_charbuf_destroy(&c);
00145     ccn_charbuf_destroy(&f);
00146     return(0);
00147 }
